    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">設防</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BUILD CITY WALLS FOR DEFENDING a PLACE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard general word for fortifying a place by building a city wall is chéng 城.</p>
<p>2. Zhù 築 refers to the building or reinforcing of city walls.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>設防</p>
<p>布防</p>
<p>鞏固</p>
<p>固</p>
<p>加強 refers to strengthening something, not necessarily for defensive purposes, and the word is marginal in the group.</p>
<p>first rough draft to identify synonym group members for future analysis, based on CL. 18.11.2003. CH</p>
        </div>
